properties.headline: SCHEDULED ROADWORK - WOOLGOOLGA TO BALLINA Pacific Highway
properties.otherAdvice:
There will also be some night works as outlined below.

From Monday, there will be five days of work next to the Pacific Highway between Tyndale and Glenugie to carry out landscape maintenance. Motorists can expect lane closures, traffic control and reduced speed limits at times between 7am and 6pm.  

From Tuesday, there will be up to four days of work on the Pacific Highway between Woodburn and Devils Pulpit to remove signs and carry out line marking and landscape maintenance. Motorists can expect lane closures, traffic control, short stoppages and reduced speed limits at times between 6am and 6pm.  

The southbound U-turn at the New Italy Museum, New Italy will be temporarily closed between 7am and 6pm for up to two days from Tuesday. The next available U-turn for southbound motorists is about one kilometre south.  

Also from Tuesday, there will be six days and nights of work on the Pacific Highway at Shark Creek to carry out maintenance on the new bridge. Motorists can expect lane closures and a contraflow arrangement at times between 6am and 6pm and 6pm and 6am.  

On Wednesday, there will be one night of work on the Pacific Highway between the Woodburn interchange and New Italy to carry out line marking. Motorists can expect lane closures, traffic control, short stoppages and a reduced speed limit at times between 6pm and 11pm.  

From Thursday, there will be up to two days of work next to the Pacific Highway at Maclean to carry out landscape maintenance in the median. Motorists can expect lane closures and traffic control at times between 6am and 6pm.

Local roads will also be affected.
